HEADWORD: Hygrometry
<hw>Hy*grom"e*try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>hygrom⟦eacute⟧trie</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>That
branch of physics which relates to the determination of the humidity of
bodies, particularly of the atmosphere, with the theory and use of the
instruments constructed for this purpose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hygrophanous</ent>⟦br⟧
